The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, December 14, 2003 				 Pep talk for insurers 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Dec. 13: IRDA chairman C. S. Rao today urged general insurance companies to look beyond the manufacturing sector and focus on the services sector. Rao said, The insurers have to adopt to the changing profile of its customers. Indian general insurance focuses on the manufacturing segment. The services sector is taking a large and growing share of Indias gross domestic product. This offers immense opportunities for expansion.																								Rao also advised new private insurance companies to focus on agriculture and come up with new products for the people in rural areas. 
